LAND
  List your land units in a human-readable table.

SYNTAX
  land [<uid-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]
  lnd  [<uid-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays a table of land units you own.  With no argument shows
  all your land units.

  <uid-spec>  - a uid, uid range, comma list, "*" for all, "~" for
                units with no army assigned, or an army letter (see
                'info army').  Note that "#N" here means uid N (not
                a realm), same as march/attack/fire.

  Two optional filters can be appended after '?' (and combined with
  '&'), matching the sector-spec '?condition' convention (info realm):

    ?realm=N    - only units currently within realm N's bounding box
                  (see 'info realm'; units use ?realm=N rather than
                  #N, since #N already means "uid N" here)
    ?type=X     - only units of type X -- matches the short type
                  code shown in 'show land' or a case-insensitive
                  substring of the full name

  Column meanings:
    lnd#           - land unit uid
    land unit type - name of unit type (infantry, armor, etc.)
    x,y            - current location (relative to your capital)
    ar             - army letter (~ means not assigned to an army;
                     see 'info army' to assign units to an army and
                     use the letter as a group selector on
                     march/attack/fire)
    eff            - efficiency 0-100%.  Builds up over time in any
                     owned sector, but only at full speed in a
                     headquarters or fortress -- everywhere else
                     it's a third the rate
    civ            - civilians carried
    mil            - military carried
    uw             - uncompensated workers carried
    fd             - food carried
    mob            - mobility points
    tech           - tech level the unit was built at

EXAMPLE
  land *                     all your land units
  lnd 0                      land unit number 0 only
  lnd 0-5                    land units 0 through 5
  land *?realm=2             all units within realm 2
  land *?type=cav            all cavalry, wherever they are
  land *?realm=2&type=cav    cavalry within realm 2 only

